    'cochlear-implant' => [
        'details' => "A cochlear implant is a small, sophisticated electronic device that restores the sensation of hearing for people with severe to profound hearing loss who no longer benefit from hearing aids. Unlike a hearing aid, which amplifies sound, a cochlear implant bypasses the damaged part of the inner ear entirely and stimulates the hearing nerve directly — sending sound signals straight to the brain.\n\nOur cochlear implant programme is led by Dr. J. M. Hans, Padma Shri awardee and one of India's foremost cochlear implant surgeons, with over 3,500 successful implant procedures spanning infants receiving their first sounds to seniors reconnecting with their families. This depth of experience matters: candidacy assessment, surgical precision and structured rehabilitation all directly influence how well a patient hears with their implant.\n\nThe surgery itself is minimally invasive and typically takes two to three hours. But we measure success by what happens afterwards — our audiologists and speech therapists work with every patient through activation, device programming (mapping) and auditory-verbal therapy, because learning to hear with an implant is a journey we walk together.",
