            ['question' => 'Is cochlear implant surgery safe?', 'answer' => 'Yes. Cochlear implantation is a well-established procedure performed worldwide for over four decades. In experienced hands the risks are low — comparable to other routine ear surgeries. Our team has performed 3,500+ implants, including complex and revision cases.'],
            ['question' => 'What is the right age for a cochlear implant?', 'answer' => 'For children born with severe hearing loss, earlier is better — ideally before 2 years of age, when the brain is most receptive to learning sound and language. There is no upper age limit for adults; we have successfully implanted patients in their 70s and 80s.'],
