            ['question' => 'How do I know if I have sinusitis or just a cold?', 'answer' => 'A common cold typically resolves within 7-10 days. If congestion, facial pressure, thick discharge or reduced smell persist beyond 10 days, or improve and then worsen again, you likely have sinusitis and should be evaluated.'],
