    'pediatric-ent' => [
        'details' => "Children are not small adults — their ears, nose and throat are still developing, their symptoms present differently, and they need a gentler, more patient approach to care. Our Pediatric ENT programme is designed around children, from the waiting room to the operating theatre.\n\nWe treat the full range of childhood ENT conditions: recurring ear infections and glue ear, enlarged tonsils and adenoids, snoring and mouth-breathing, speech delay related to hearing, and congenital conditions. Every child receives an age-appropriate evaluation, and we take time to explain findings clearly to parents — including when the right answer is to wait and watch rather than treat.\n\nWhen procedures like grommet insertion, tonsillectomy or adenoidectomy are needed, they are performed with pediatric anaesthesia protocols and same-day discharge wherever possible, so your child recovers in the comfort of home. Our audiologists and speech therapists complete the circle of care for children with hearing and speech concerns.",
